oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Health, Productivity, and Management of Calves on Ontario Beef Cow-Calf Herds
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Alves, David M.
McDermott, John J.
Anderson, Neil G.
Martin, S. Wayne
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: calf health
production data
production
management practices
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This presentation is based on a preliminary analysis of calf health and production data from an observational study of 200 cow-calf herds (1986-88) in Ontario, Canada. The purpose of this paper is to present common levels of calf mortality/morbidity and production from birth to weaning, common levels of calf management practices, and preliminary identification of factors affecting calf health and production on cow-calf farms.
